<div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
								
	<p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
	<p n="1-7">Fifth year, current <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cellā niṉṟa</foreign></supplied>, <gap reason="ellipsis"/> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tiru-v-eḻutt-iṭṭu</foreign></supplied>, of the king Parakesarivarman.</p>
	<p n="7-25">The gold that I, ..., gave, in the custody <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vacam</foreign></supplied> of the members of the assembly of Rājāśrayacaturvedimaṅgala <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Cēlam, for one perpetual lamp for the great Lord of the temple of ... in Cēlam <supplied reason="subaudible">is</supplied> five <foreign>kaḻañcu</foreign>s.</p>
	<p n="25-28">He who injures this pious donation <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>taṉmam</foreign><note>Sanskrit <foreign>dharma</foreign>.</note></supplied> will know sin.</p>
	
</div>
	
